result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Stryder A. Winch in court with attorney William George Weiland. Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.  Cases 15CM345 and 13CM458 and Statement of Uncharged Read-Ins.
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.

Defendant enters a plea of: 15CM458 Count 1 & 2: No Contest

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty 15CM458.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date. 15CM345 and uncharged read ins are Dismissed and Read In.

ADA Constable requests the joint recommendation be adopted by the Court and the victims want contact with Defendant. 
Atty Weiland concurs with joint recommendation. 

BY THE COURT:******PROBATION******
15CM458 Count 1: 946.49(1)(a) Misd. Bail Jump:
W/H Sentence: 12 mo Probation (1 day jail credit)
Conditions:
Pay costs + DNA surcharge = $443.00
AODA & comply with treatment recommendations.  
Maintain absolute sobriety with regards to alcohol and illegal drugs.  
Participate in any counseling recommended by the agent.

15CM458: Count 2: 947.01(1) Misd. Disorderly Conduct
W/H Sentence: 12 mo Probation, concurrent with count 1
Conditions: (same conditions as Ct 1).
Pay costs + DNA surcharge = $443.00
